defaultThe Benefits of MPAsdefault4.3 Increasingly, it is not only the declining health and productivity of the marine environment that has been well documented.
default A wealth of scientific 
defaultand economic 
defaultevidence is emerging validating the important role that 
defaultMarine Protected Areas (MPAs)
default can play in fostering recovery. 
defaultWell-managed 
defaultMPAs
default can be thought of as ‘ecological bank accounts’, enabling the recovery of ‘capital’, while continuing to support local industries through the overspill of ‘interest’. 
defaultA scientific review of 
defaultMPA
default performance in 2009 revealed that MPAs produced on average a 450% increase in biomass, 120% increase in abundance, and 20% increase in biodiversity
default.
default defaultWithin the UK:
